// Purpose:  This program is provided as a simple example and starting point for basic 
//           ROV drive software.  It is intended for underwater robotics teams to help
//           them quickly get a new simple ROV up and running, and can be enhanced and
//           customized to add features such as automatic depth control, switchable
//           max power level modes, tilt control, switchable diagnostics modes, etc.
//
// Notes:    1) In its initial, simple configuration, this program is intended to work on
//              an ROV with the following basic configuration:
//               - Playstation 2 (PS/2) controller.
//               - 4 HORIZONTAL Blue Robotics (brushless) thrusters
//                    (mounted in a vectored configuration).
//               - 2 VERTICAL Blue Robotics (brushless) thrusters.
//               - Arduino Mega and six Blue Robotics ESCs, all mounted in a control
//                      box on land (in the dry).
//               - Single gripper, controlled by a standard servo.
//
//           2) The PS2X_lib.h Arduino library is needed in order to read the inputs from the PS/2 controller.
//              PS/2 controllers are ideal for this simple configuration because their output is analog,
//              and they can be hooked directly to an Arduino.  See Bill Porter's web page for more 
//              information on this library:
//              http://www.billporter.info/2010/06/05/playstation-2-controller-arduino-library-v1-0/.
//
// Questions:  If you have questions about this code or about how to build a basic ROV, please feel free to
//             contact Ned Voorhees by email at ned (at) triad.rr.com or ned.voorhees (at) gmail.com.
//
